    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-11-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-11-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="1811"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1811">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 367.11/28a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of the Navy</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 8, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I have the honor, in pursuance of instructions that I have received from the
                    President, to request you to be good enough to despatch two vessels with the
                    least possible delay to the ports of Beirut and <pb facs="1463" n="1347"
                        xml:id="pg_1347"/> Smyrna to protect or to give refuge to American citizens
                    in case of antiforeign outbreaks there, subject, however, to any supplemental
                    requests the American Embassy at Constantinople may make.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Approved. <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wm. H. Taft.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
